  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">UNHCR Secondment - Field Protection Officer in Maban County, Upper Nile State</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">Over 168,000 Sudanese refugees have sought protection in South Sudan and are currently hosted in 7 settlements in Upper Nile and Unity States. Military opera-tions and the depletion of food resources are causes of their flight. In the absence of a national legal framework for the protection of refugees or institutional structures for managing the emergency, UNHCR and its partners are ensuring that the most urgent life-saving needs are met. UNHCR has engaged over 20 implementing partners to assist with protection and assistance activities. Among key protection challenges are to ensure relocation of arriving refugees fur-ther inland, as border crossings (ex. El Foj) are subject to aerial bombardment; ensure civilian character of settlements and prevent and limit the risks for girls and women, when collecting wood or fetching water.</narrative>
  </description>
